<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-13-0841 </DOCNO><TEXT>This report is based on lectures presented on the 17th World Gas Conferenceheld in Washington from 5-9 June, 1988, information from some technicalsessions, the exposition and informal chats. Successively the followingitems are discussed: optimism about the future of natural gas; spectaculargrowth of natural gas supplies; uncertainties about gas supplies in WesternEurope. Then some technological developments are discussed. Also attentionis paid to problems in less developed countries concerning the gas production.It is concluded that these conferences are very interesting and usefulfor non-technologists. The report ends with a long list of titles fromreports and papers presented at the conference. 2 figs.</TEXT></DOC>